A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 State Designations – State Amphibian – Long–Tailed Salamander
3 FOR the purpose of designating the long–tailed salamander as the State amphibian; and
4 generally relating to a State amphibian.
5 BY renumbering
6 Article – General Provisions
7 Section 7–301 through 7–310
8 to be Section 7–302 through 7–311, respectively
9 Annotated Code of Maryland
10 (2019 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
11 BY adding to
12 Article – General Provisions
13 Section 7–301
14 Annotated Code of Maryland
15 (2019 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
16 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
17 That Section(s) 7–301 through 7–310 of Article – General Provisions of the Annotated Code
18 of Maryland be renumbered to be Section(s) 7–302 through 7–311, respectively.
19 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That the Laws of Maryland read
20 as follows:
21 Article – General Provisions
22 7–301.
23 THE LONG–TAILED SALAMANDER (EURYCEA LONGICAUDA) IS THE STATE
